Collection Frameworks (arrays,sets etc)
    - it provides a interface and classes that help in managing group of objects.

 Before the introduction of the Collection Framework in JDK 1.2,
  Java used to rely on a variety of classes like Vector, Stack, Hashtable, and arrays
   to store and manipulate groups of objects.

However these individual classes had several drawbacks :

1  • Inconsistency: Each class had a different way of managing collections, leading to confusion
        and a steep learning curve.
2  • Lack of inter-operability: These classes were not designed to work together seamlessly.(no interconnection)
3  • No common interface: There was no common interface for all these classes, which meant
        you couldn't write generic algorithms that could operate on different types of collections.

