iterable and collection are frameworks
# 1. Lists is a interface jisko implement karti hai kuch classes jese ki ArrayList , LinkedList , Vector , Stack
    - rmbr : these are classes so 1st letter capital.
        - List = ordered collection
eg ArrayList<int> => ArrayList and other classes of collection framework expects wrapper class i.e Class ke andar bhi class ki chahiye
 so ArrayList<Integer> is correct way to declare in java.

# 2. Set is a interface : implemented by some classes like HashSet , LinkedHashSet , EnumSet , TreeSet , SortedSet.
      - Set = unique values

# 3. Map interface - HashMap , LinkedHashMap  , HashTable
      - Map : Key-Value pairs.

// interface we very well know is a skeleton or structure from which classes can inherit .